bug.short_desc: the servlet-bridge disable the security role mapping in websphere 6.1

long_desc.thetext:
if there is roles defined in the bridge ear, in websphere 6.1 manager console, there will be an item to setup role user mapping.
once the bridge is startup, the setup page is missing.
The reason is the OSGi in the bridge overwrites the URLStreamHandler of the OSGi in websphere.
1. When WAS starts up, it registers a URLStreamHandler to handle the bundle:// URL.
2. The WAS admin uses the URLHandler to load the DTD in application.xml, the DTD is bundleresource://25/application_1_4.xsd which is correct in WAS.
3. When Bridge starts up, it also registers a URLStreamHandler to handle the bundle:// URL.
4. The WAS admin uses the bridges' URLStreamHandler to load the DTD. As the WAS has different bundles with the Bridge, the bundleresource://25/application_1_4.xsd is not invalid in bridge's OSGi, so the loading failed.
Created attachment 86437 screen shot of was admin console and the application.xml used to create the EAR

The URLStreamHandlerFactory that's installed by the ServletBridge is meant to respect the callers context so that if only WAS classes are on the stack the SB's "bundle" URLStreamHandler should not be consulted.
Can you provide the exact version of the framework bundle used in the EAR. e.g. what version of org.eclipse.osgi
It would also help if you could provide the version of WAS being used. Is it fully patched? What version is the org.eclipse.osgi bundle in WebSphere/AppServer/plugins
A similar sounding bug was fixed last fall and I want to eliminate that possibility first.
Also, if you can provide a small EAR file that would help to reproduce the problem.
Websphere version:6.1.0.0 OSGi in WAS: org.eclipse.osgi_3.1.2.jar OSGi in EAR: org.eclipse.osgi_3.3.1R33x_v20070828.jar
Created attachment 86540 EAR file to reproduce the problem

Hi Wei,
Thanks for your test case. I tried this on Express 6.1.0.3 and was not able to reproduce the problem you're seeing. Would it be possible for you to try using an updated release.
FYI- The version of OSGi being used in my install was org.eclipse.osgi_3.2.1.R32x_v20060919.jar.
Wei, I'm marking this as WORKS FOR ME although I'm curious if upgrading resolved your issue. If there's more to this bug we can re-open.
